    "notes": [
        "<b>Writing Intensive Courses:</b> Students must take 3 courses: 1 First Year (UWRT-150 or ISTE-110), 1 Gen Ed, & 1 program specific (CSCI-472)",
        "<b>Lab Sciences:</b> Only specific sequences are allowed in Biology, Chemistry or Physics. Please see the CS/SE BS/MS course page.",
        "<b>CS and SE Electives:</b> Only specific courses are allowed. Please see the CS and SE handbooks or talk to an academic advisor.",
        "<b>BS/MS Double-Counted Courses:</b> Identified with a leading *.",
        "<u><b>Swapping:</b> Note that if 1, 2 or 3 CSCI graduate (cluster) electives are taken to satisfy SE Graduate Elective requirements, correspondingly 1, 2 or 3 of the double-count courses can be moved from Open Elective and subbed in to satisfy CSCI (cluster) electives.</u>"
    ]
